org.hackystat.utilities.uricache
Class UriCache<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  org.hackystat.utilities.uricache.UriCache<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - type of the cache keys.
V - type of the cache items.
public class UriCache<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object

Provides an easy caching mechanism which is backed by Apache JCS (Java Caching System). Once cache configured and initialized, it caches pairs <K, V>. Note that both K and V types must be Serializable.

Using an UriCache has several advantages: it increases performance as it reduces URL lookups.

Author:
Pavel Senin
